The error is at the end of the proof of `liftContext_run`. The tactic `sorry` is used, indicating that the proof is incomplete.

We need to prove the equality:
```tactics
⊢ (do
      let a ← runToRound (Fin.last n) (lens.stmt.toFunA outerStmtIn) (lens.wit.toFunA (outerStmtIn, outerWitIn)) P
      Prod.mk a.1 <;> (lens.lift (outerStmtIn, outerWitIn) <;> P.output a.2).liftComp (oSpec + fun i => pSpec.Type ↑i)) =
    do
    let a ← runToRound (Fin.last n) (lens.stmt.toFunA outerStmtIn) (lens.wit.toFunA (outerStmtIn, outerWitIn)) P
    (fun a_1 => (a.1, lens.lift (outerStmtIn, outerWitIn) a_1)) <;> (P.output a.2).liftComp (oSpec + fun i => pSpec.Type ↑i)
```

The left side is:
```tactics
let a := runToRound (Fin.last n) (lens.stmt.toFunA outerStmtIn) (lens.wit.toFunA (outerStmtIn, outerWitIn)) P
Prod.mk a.1 <;> (lens.lift (outerStmtIn, outerWitIn) <;> P.output a.2).liftComp (oSpec + fun i => pSpec.Type ↑i)
```

The right side is:
```tactics
let a := runToRound (Fin.last n) (lens.stmt.toFunA outerStmtIn) (lens.wit.toFunA (outerStmtIn, outerWitIn)) P
(fun a_1 => (a.1, lens.lift (outerStmtIn, outerWitIn) a_1)) <;> (P.output a.2).liftComp (oSpec + fun i => pSpec.Type ↑i)
```

These are definitionally equal because `Prod.mk x y` is definitionally equal to `⟨x, y⟩` and `fun x => (x, y)` is definitionally equal to `fun x => ⟨x, y⟩`. The rest of the structure is the same.

We can prove this using the `simp` tactic, which will simplify both sides and show they are equal.

```tactics
