The `sorry` is on the last line of the theorem `liftContext_run`. We need to replace this with a valid proof.

Looking at the goal state:
`⊢ (do ... ) = do ...`
This is an equality between two `do` blocks. The first `do` block is the left side, and the second is the right side.

Left side:
`do let a ← runToRound (Fin.last n) (lens.stmt.toFunA outerStmtIn) (lens.wit.toFunA (outerStmtIn, outerWitIn)) P; Prod.mk a.1 <;> (lens.lift (outerStmtIn, outerWitIn) <;> P.output a.2).liftComp (oSpec + fun i => pSpec.Type ↑i)`

Right side:
`do let a ← runToRound (Fin.last n) (lens.stmt.toFunA outerStmtIn) (lens.wit.toFunA (outerStmtIn, outerWitIn)) P; (fun a_1 => (a.1, lens.lift (outerStmtIn, outerWitIn) a_1)) <;> (P.output a.2).liftComp (oSpec + fun i => pSpec.Type ↑i)`

These are definitionally equal. The `Prod.mk` on the left is equivalent to the anonymous function on the right. The rest of the structure is the same.

We can prove this using `simp` and `congr`.

